{
  "text": "The binding of TbRIII (a heparan sulfate proteoglycan) (35) to Nrp1-Fc was prevented by heparin ( Figure 1E ), suggesting that Nrp1 was binding the heparan sulfate groups of TbRIII. Indeed, Nrp1 has affinity for heparin and heparan sulfate [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Heparin failed to block binding of TbRI-Fc in the same experiment ( Figure 1E) .",
  "correct_citation": {
